{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Jhon-Crow/cassette-sound-music-player/pulls/30","id":3184821071,"node_id":"PR_kwDOQx6vn8691INP","html_url":"https://github.com/Jhon-Crow/cassette-sound-music-player/pull/30","diff_url":"https://github.com/Jhon-Crow/cassette-sound-music-player/pull/30.diff","patch_url":"https://github.com/Jhon-Crow/cassette-sound-music-player/pull/30.patch","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Jhon-Crow/cassette-sound-music-player/issues/30","number":30,"state":"open","locked":false,"title":"Fix: Improve button hit detection for mobile and small windows","user":{"login":"konard","id":1431904,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1431904?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard","html_url":"https://github.com/konard","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"body":"## üéØ Summary\n\nThis PR fixes issue #28 by significantly improving button hit detection on mobile devices and in small windows.\n\n## üìã Issue Reference\nFixes #28\n\n## üîç Problem\n\nPreviously, the buttons on the cassette player were extremely difficult to click/tap on mobile devices and in small windows because:\n- The visual buttons are very small 3D objects (0.010 x 0.004 x 0.007 units)\n- Click/tap detection used precise raycasting against these tiny geometries\n- There was no tolerance or padding around the clickable areas\n\n## ‚úÖ Solution\n\nAdded invisible collision boxes around each button that are approximately 3x larger (0.014 x 0.012 x 0.012 units) than the visual buttons. These collision boxes:\n- Are completely invisible (transparent material with visible: false)\n- Extend the clickable area above, below, and around each button\n- Share the same button type userData, so they trigger the same actions\n- Make touch targets much more forgiving on mobile devices\n\n## üìù Implementation Details\n\n**File Modified:** `src/renderer.js`\n\nChanges made in the `createCassettePlayer()` function:\n1. Added collision box geometry for each of the 4 control buttons (prev, play, stop, next)\n2. Added collision box for the play button's red dot indicator\n3. Each collision box is positioned at the same location as its corresponding visual button\n4. All collision boxes have `userData.isButton = true` and the appropriate `buttonType` for proper raycasting detection\n\n## üß™ Testing\n\nThe solution was verified by:\n- Reviewing the button creation code and collision detection logic\n- Ensuring collision boxes are properly registered for raycasting\n- Confirming the visual appearance remains unchanged (collision boxes are invisible)\n- Verifying that both desktop and mobile click/touch handlers will detect these larger hit areas\n\n## üí° Technical Notes\n\n- The visual buttons remain the same size - only the clickable area is enlarged\n- The collision boxes use `MeshBasicMaterial` with `visible: false` for zero rendering cost\n- The approach works for both mouse clicks (desktop) and touch events (mobile)\n- No changes to the raycasting logic were needed - the existing system automatically detects the larger collision boxes\n\n---\n*This PR was created automatically by the AI issue solver*","created_at":"2026-01-18T01:27:55Z","updated_at":"2026-01-18T01:41:44Z","closed_at":null,"merged_at":null,"merge_commit_sha":"95cd326c37907b1a8c7e90a1